import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='y', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['y'].mean(), color='red', label=f'mean={data["y"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between x and y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    quadrant_count = data.groupby('quadrant').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='quadrant', y='count', data=quadrant_count)
    plt.title('What is the most common quadrant in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    for index, row in quadrant_count.iterrows():
        chart.text(row.name,row['count'], round(row['count'],2), color='black', ha="center")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='x', data=data)
    plt.axvline(data['x'].min(), color='red', label=f"Min: {data['x'].min().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].max(), color='green', label=f"Max: {data['x'].max().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='blue', label=f"Median: {data['x'].median().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the range of x values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
